data.content:
Scotiabank
Scotiabank is a financial institution that issues the Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card, which offers Collision/Loss Damage Insurance to cardholders.<SEP>Scotiabank is the policyholder of the Group Policy No. BNS0194, offering benefits through the ScotiaGold Passport VISA.

First North American Insurance Company
First North American Insurance Company is the insurer providing collision/loss damage insurance under Policy BNS750 for Scotiabank cardholders.

The Manufacturers Life Insurance Company (Manulife)
Manulife is the parent company of First North American Insurance Company, which provides insurance coverage for Scotiabank cardholders.

Bank of Nova Scotia
The Bank of Nova Scotia is the formal name for Scotiabank, which is involved in providing insurance coverage via its Visa Commercial Card.

data.entity_name: Canadian Dollar Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card
data.content:
Canadian Dollar Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card
The Canadian Dollar Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card is a credit card issued by Scotiabank used for commercial transactions, including vehicle rentals.<SEP>This is a type of credit card issued by Scotiabank that offers benefits such as Collision/Loss Damage Insurance for rentals.

Collision/Loss Damage Insurance
Collision/Loss Damage Insurance is a type of coverage provided when renting a vehicle using the Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card, protecting against loss or damage to the rental vehicle.<SEP>Collision/Loss Damage Insurance provides coverage for damages or loss to rental vehicles under certain conditions.<SEP>This insurance covers loss or damage to rental vehicles for cardholders who decline the Rental Agency's Collision Damage Waiver.

Car Sharing
Car Sharing is a service where members have 24-hour access to a fleet of cars, and it is included under the term 'rental agency' in the insurance policy.<SEP>Car Sharing refers to a car rental club that provides members with 24-hour access to a fleet of cars.

Central Travel Account (CTA)
A Central Travel Account is used by companies to manage travel bookings, and it can be used to qualify for Collision/Loss Damage Insurance.<SEP>An account type that allows multiple designated users to rent vehicles, with coverage limited to one vehicle per user.

Rental Agency
A Rental Agency is a business entity that provides vehicles for rent to customers under specific terms and conditions. These agencies are licensed auto rental services that may require deposits and offer optional coverage options, such as Collision Damage Waivers (CDW), to protect against potential vehicle damages. Furthermore, Rental Agencies are involved in managing vehicle rentals, which includes addressing any vehicle damage and handling claims related to repairs, theft, and Loss of Use charges.<SEP>A rental agency is a business that rents vehicles to customers, and in this context, is involved in the insurance claims process for damages or theft of rental vehicles.<SEP>The rental agency is the company providing the rental car service and handling rental agreements.

Rental Agency's CDW
The Rental Agency's CDW is an optional coverage offered by rental companies to relieve renters of financial responsibility for damage or theft.

Tax-Free Car
A tax-free car is a short-term vehicle lease agreement for tourists, which is not covered by the Collision/Loss Damage Insurance program.

Eligible Person
An Eligible Person is a cardholder or authorized driver who meets specific conditions to qualify for Collision/Loss Damage Insurance.

Loss of Use
Loss of Use refers to charges incurred when a rental car is unavailable for rental due to damage.<SEP>Loss of Use refers to charges related to the inability to use a vehicle due to damage, which may be covered under certain insurance claims.<SEP>Loss of Use refers to compensation paid to a Rental Agency when a rental vehicle is unavailable due to repairs after damage during the rental period.<SEP>Loss of Use refers to the charges incurred by a rental agency when a vehicle is unavailable for rental due to damage or theft.

Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card
The Scotiabank Visa Commercial Card is a financial product that provides certain insurance coverages for car rentals when used for transactions.

Manulife
Manulife is an insurance company committed to protecting customer privacy and handling personal information for administering coverage and processing claims.<SEP>Manulife is an insurance company involved in processing claims related to vehicle rental damages.<SEP>Manulife is an insurance company responsible for administering claims related to the Collision/Loss Damage Insurance.<SEP>Manulife is an insurance company that provides administrative support for claims related to the Scotiabank Visa* Commercial Card.

Canadian dollar
The Canadian dollar is the currency required for transactions to activate the Collision/Loss Damage Insurance coverage.

Tax-Free Car Package
A tax-free car package that allows tourists to lease vehicles for short-term periods, offering a guaranteed buyback option.

Canadian Dollar
The currency required for transactions to activate the Collision/Loss Damage Insurance coverage.

Travel Card
A card with a single authorized cardholder, providing coverage for one rental vehicle at a time.

Scotiabank Commercial Account
Scotiabank Commercial Account refers to the financial account provided by Scotiabank, which offers various commercial banking services.

Coverage
Coverage refers to the insurance protection provided under specific terms, including limitations and exclusions, for rental vehicles.

Eligible Persons
Eligible Persons are individuals who meet specific criteria to qualify for insurance coverage under the Scotiabank policy.

Third Party Liability
Third Party Liability refers to the legal responsibility for damages or injuries to another party, which is not covered by this insurance policy.

Replacement Vehicle
Replacement Vehicle refers to a vehicle rented to replace another vehicle, which is not covered if personal insurance covers the cost.

Rental Period
Rental Period is the duration for which a vehicle is rented, with coverage limitations if it exceeds 48 consecutive days.

Narcotic Influence
Narcotic Influence refers to operating a vehicle while under the influence of narcotics, which voids coverage.

Seizure or Destruction
Seizure or Destruction refers to the confiscation or destruction of the vehicle under quarantine, customs, or government orders, which is not covered.

War and Hostile Actions
War and Hostile Actions refer to damages arising from war-like actions, insurrections, or government actions, which are excluded from coverage.

Nuclear Reaction
Nuclear Reaction refers to damages caused by nuclear reactions, radiation, or contamination, which are not covered by this insurance policy.

Scotiabank Visa* Commercial Card
The Scotiabank Visa* Commercial Card is a financial service product that offers rental vehicle coverage and other benefits.

Canada
Canada is a country in North America where the coverage and services of the Scotiabank Visa* Commercial Card are available.<SEP>Canada is a country where specific contact numbers are provided for reporting insurance claims related to rental vehicle damage or theft.

Accident/Theft Event
An accident or theft event is an incident involving damage or loss of a rental vehicle, triggering the need for a claim.

Global Excel Management
Global Excel Management is an administrator appointed by Manulife to handle assistance and claims services under the insurance certificate.<SEP>Global Excel Management is responsible for handling documentation related to insurance claims for Manulife.

CDW (Collision Damage Waiver)
CDW is an optional insurance coverage offered by rental agencies to cover damages to rental vehicles.

Windsor, ON
Windsor, ON is the location where Global Excel Management processes insurance claim documentation.

Privacy Officer, Manulife
The Privacy Officer at Manulife is responsible for managing requests to review and correct personal information contained in Manulife's files.

Waterloo, ON
Waterloo, ON is the location of Manulife's offices where personal information files are secured.

The Bank of Nova Scotia
The Bank of Nova Scotia is a licensed user of Visa International, mentioned in the context of the insurance document.<SEP>The Bank of Nova Scotia, also known as Scotiabank, is a Canadian multinational bank offering financial services including the ScotiaGold VISA.

Active Claims Management (2018) Inc.
Active Claims Management (2018) Inc., operating as Active Care Management, ACM, Global Excel Management, and/or Global Excel, is appointed by Manulife to provide assistance and claims services.

data.entity_name: In the Event of an Accident/Theft
data.content:
In the Event of an Accident/Theft
The procedures outlined for reporting and handling vehicle accidents or theft, including claims processing.

Primmum Insurance Company
Primmum Insurance Company is the insurer providing the Group Policy for the ScotiaGold Passport VISA Rental Car Insurance.

World Travel Protection Canada Inc.
World Travel Protection Canada Inc. provides services under the Group Policy as the Group Policy administrator.

ScotiaGold Passport VISA
ScotiaGold Passport VISA is a credit card offering rental car collision/loss damage insurance and other benefits.

Toronto, Ontario
Toronto is a city in Ontario, Canada, where the ScotiaGold VISA Auto Rental CLD Insurance office is located.<SEP>Toronto, Ontario is the location of the Executive Offices of Scotiabank where the Group Policy is on file.

Tax-free Car
Tax-free Car is a package offering tourists a short-term, tax-free vehicle lease agreement with a guaranteed buyback.

Scotia Assist
Scotia Assist is a service associated with ScotiaGold VISA, responsible for handling auto rental insurance claims.<SEP>Scotia Assist is the administrator of the Group Policy for the ScotiaGold Passport VISA.

Scotia Rewards Points
Scotia Rewards Points are a rewards program that can be used to pay for car rentals under the ScotiaGold Passport VISA benefits.

Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)
Collision Damage Waiver is a provision that cardholders must decline to be eligible for the ScotiaGold VISA insurance coverage.

Loss Damage Waiver (LDW)
Loss Damage Waiver is a provision similar to CDW that must be declined for insurance eligibility under the ScotiaGold VISA.

Deductible Waiver
Deductible Waiver is a provision that must be waived in certain locations for ScotiaGold VISA insurance coverage to apply.

ScotiaGold VISA CLD Insurance
ScotiaGold VISA CLD Insurance is a primary insurance provider that covers liabilities related to rental vehicles, including damages, theft, and certain charges, under specific conditions and limitations.

Mini-van
A mini-van is a type of automobile classified by manufacturers or government authorities as designed to transport up to eight passengers, including the driver.

Exotic Cars
Exotic cars refer to high-end, luxury vehicles with limited production, such as Ferrari, Aston Martin, and Lamborghini, which are not covered by the insurance.

United States
The United States is a country where specific contact numbers are provided for reporting insurance claims related to rental vehicle damage or theft.

Claims Administrator
The Claims Administrator is responsible for processing insurance claims, gathering necessary information, and assisting customers in the claims process.

Towing Charges
Towing Charges are costs associated with towing a damaged or stolen rental vehicle, covered under the insurance policy.

Administration Charges
Administration Charges refer to fees charged by a rental agency for processing claims related to vehicle damage or theft.

Malicious Vandalism
Malicious Vandalism refers to intentional damage caused to a rental vehicle, covered under the insurance policy.

Theft
Theft refers to the unlawful taking of a rental vehicle, which is covered by the insurance policy under specific conditions.

Helpful Hints
Helpful Hints is a section providing tips to avoid challenges in using the insurance coverage for rental vehicles.

ScotiaGold VISA
ScotiaGold VISA is a credit card service offered by The Bank of Nova Scotia, providing auto rental insurance coverage.

Group Policy
The Group Policy refers to the insurance terms and conditions provided by ScotiaGold VISA for auto rental coverage.

Driver's Licence
The driver's licence is required as proof of identity for the person driving the car at the time of the accident.

Police Report
The police report is a document detailing the circumstances of the accident, necessary for claim processing.

Loss/Damage Report
The loss/damage report is completed with the rental agency to document any damage or loss incurred.

ScotiaGold VISA Card
The ScotiaGold VISA Card is a credit card that provides benefits including auto rental insurance coverage.

Rental Agreement
The rental agreement is a contract between the rental agency and the customer, outlining terms of the car rental.

Repair Estimate and Bills
These documents provide itemized costs for repairs to the rental vehicle, required for insurance claims.
